'God said, "Behold,<f caller="+"> <fr>1:29 </fr><ft>"Behold", from "הִנֵּה", means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an interjection.</ft></f> I have given you every herb yielding seed, which is on the surface of all the earth, and every tree, which bears fruit yielding seed. It will be your food.',
'To every animal of the earth, and to every bird of the sky, and to everything that creeps on the earth, in which there is life, I have given every green herb for food;" and it was so.',
